                <td bgcolor="#333366" valign="top"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/02/2002&nbsp;: 06:52:22 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> WTD is a nice in theory. The idea has been posted on this board before <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=7928" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=7928</a> (note: the link is no longer working with this new board it seems).<br /><br />Basically it was intended to be some sort of charm that works on corpses (necros had charm in the old days). The way VI implemented that idea simply sucks though. <br />ONLY mobs that can be charmed by enchanters should be WTDable. Furthermore these 'pets' should do their full regular damage. So if a chanter charms a mob that doubles for 500, then the WTDmob should double for 500 too. The max duration of 90 sec goes in line with that.<br /><br />The idea was to have a very minor version of chanter charm and NOT a Flaming-Sword-of-Xuzl-clone.<br /><br />Neric the Heretic<br />Arch Lich of Darkwind<br />Antonius Bayle<br /></span></font></td>
